summary: An Ordinance providing for the laying off, extending and establishing of Patten Place, in the City of Seattle, as a public street and highway, over Lot Four (4), Block Two Hundred Five (205) Gilman's Addition to the City of Seattle, and providing for the taking and damaging of land and other property necessary therefor, and for the ascertainment and payment of the just compensation to be made for the private property to be taken or damaged for said purpose and providing for payment therefor.
